AmaZulu impressed many by finishing as runners-up in the DStv Premiership last season. That has now become something the club president expects of them every year. Usuthu's owner, Sandile Zungu wants nothing less than a third-place finish, at the end of the 2021/22 season. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - AmaZulu are well on track for a third-place finish in the DStv Premiership, that's according to Usuthu owner, Sandile Zungu. The KZN outfit made two signings in the current transfer market, as they target a Caf competitions spot. READ: McCarthy's fine season at AmaZulu Usuthu finished second place last season, qualifying for their first-ever Caf Champions League, where they’ve already secured a place in the Group stage.